Rules:
The snapshot table name should be snap_ + the source table name.
The surrogate key should be called the source table name. + _key.
The surrogate key should be generated in the Dbt SQL file using the Key Columns specified in the Wiki.
There should be at least two and at most three CTE's (Common Table Expressions) in the SQL file, in the following order: source, dedup, final. The dedup CTE is optional.
The source CTE should filter out rows where all of the columns in the key are either null, or, if the column is of data type string, null or zero length string.
The name of the Dbt YAML file should be snap_ + the source table name + .yml
The name of the Dbt SQL file should be snap_ + the source table name + .sql
The name of the snapshot within the Dbt YAML file should be snap_ + the source table name
The name of the snapshot within the Dbt SQL file should be snap_ + the source table name


